Two clarifications on my original message about this subject, as people
have asked: First, Berkeley.EDU is an MX (with server ucbvax.Berkeley.EDU),
not a CNAME.  Second, the NIC host table lists Berkeley.EDU as an alias
for ucbvax.Berkeley.EDU.

Yes, to answer Steve, we received complaints from hosttable-only sites
that we were sending out mail with non-canonical names, and in particular,
one site had stripped all aliases from the host table "because it was too big".
However, as long as this hack was for the benefit of the hosttable world,
we switched to ucbvax.Berkeley.EDU.  So although your scheme is otherwise
just fine, you might want to have CS.UMD.EDU listed as a canonical name
in the host table.  (This opinion expressed only on your naming setup,
I can't say anything about smail and/or uucp stuff.)

		Mike

